            <thetext>When copying files (e.g. through &#39;copy-files&#39; and &#39;copy-resources&#39; key 
processing) there is a certain set of files and/or directories that is being 
skipped, e.g. version control directories like .svn/ and .git/.

As it is not always forseeable which files and directories should be ignored in 
any given environment, it would be nice to allow the user to configure in 
config.json a list of file and directory patterns that should be skipped during 
file copying.

There could be  a macro SKIP_FILES that holds the list of patterns, which is 
then referenced in the copy-files and copy-resources keys. A suitable default 
list could be given as the fall-back value, like [&#39;^\.svn$&#39;, &#39;^_svn$&#39;, &#39;^CVS$&#39;, 
&#39;^\.git$&#39;, &#39;^\.DS_Store$&#39;].</thetext>
          </long_desc>
